00:45:03,593 --> 00:45:04,452
My friend.

532
00:45:16,825 --> 00:45:17,700
Who are you?

533
00:45:20,589 --> 00:45:21,777
You came too early

534
00:45:22,464 --> 00:45:23,074
Get out.

535
00:45:23,495 --> 00:45:24,363
Hold on.

536
00:45:26,782 --> 00:45:28,321
I need to wear.

537
00:45:28,595 --> 00:45:30,377
Get out.
You are always naked.

538
00:45:30,830 --> 00:45:35,908
By the way, he says he'd much rather have my body than yours.

539
00:45:38,944 --> 00:45:40,897
If you're so disappointed, why don't you try it with your body?

540
00:45:41,928 --> 00:45:46,139
I'll pay you back later.

541
00:45:48,982 --> 00:45:53,928
You sleep with women to use them.
You wanted to know who my client was last night, so you dragged her into it.

542
00:46:02,898 --> 00:46:07,296
What the hell are you?
Did you approach me in a seductive way to take advantage of me?

543
00:46:12,730 --> 00:46:15,347
I wanted to change my job to another more upscale bar.

544
00:46:15,636 --> 00:46:18,425
No.
You want to do something with Nanbada.

545
00:46:18,894 --> 00:46:21,949
You're using me to get the president to trust you and find out what's going on.

546
00:46:30,493 --> 00:46:33,821
Don't make fun of me.
I'll tell him you are spy.

547
00:46:37,540 --> 00:46:38,462
What are you going to do with me?

548
00:46:52,737 --> 00:46:53,909
Destroy me?

549
00:46:54,893 --> 00:46:56,885
I can't.

550
00:46:57,401 --> 00:47:01,010
I loved it.

551
00:47:14,580 --> 00:47:18,010
Ube.
You can tell me everything now.

552
00:47:20,557 --> 00:47:22,393
You are not capable of doing anything wrong.

553
00:47:25,447 --> 00:47:30,596
We have a certain person marked as the mastermind behind your appointment to the board of directors.

554
00:47:31,386 --> 00:47:36,003
We believe that you were merely taken advantage of in the recent UKIYOSHI case.

555
00:47:39,665 --> 00:47:41,352
Tell me,Ube.

556
00:47:48,337 --> 00:47:49,806
Hello, Osaki room.

557
00:47:57,360 --> 00:47:57,923
Who are you?

558
00:48:00,931 --> 00:48:01,665
I'll ask him.

559
00:48:09,822 --> 00:48:13,150
Your son is Ichiro?

560
00:48:14,493 --> 00:48:17,353
Is something wrong with Ichiro?

561
00:48:18,525 --> 00:48:21,283
The hospital informed me that he's dying.

562
00:48:22,056 --> 00:48:23,415
Really?

563
00:48:25,917 --> 00:48:28,964
I want to meet him.

564
00:48:29,886 --> 00:48:31,011
Please.

565
00:49:34,615 --> 00:49:35,771
Are you alright?

566
00:49:36,396 --> 00:49:37,302
Wait.

567
00:49:37,833 --> 00:49:38,763
Wait.

568
00:49:40,746 --> 00:49:41,504
Are you alright?

569
00:49:47,816 --> 00:49:50,754
That was stupid of him to get called out on a fake phone call.

570
00:49:51,746 --> 00:49:54,605
I'm sorry.

571
00:49:56,480 --> 00:50:00,386
Ube was murdered.
The Far East Credit Union case is over.

572
00:50:04,129 --> 00:50:05,215
I'll find who did it.

573
00:50:06,829 --> 00:50:10,712
Osaki,The murderer has turned himself in.

574
00:50:11,884 --> 00:50:12,579
Really?

575
00:50:15,165 --> 00:50:16,439
How many times have I told you?

576
00:50:17,384 --> 00:50:20,126
My brother works for the company that went under.

577
00:50:20,728 --> 00:50:23,251
They don't even get a severance package.

578
00:50:24,275 --> 00:50:27,056
That's when I started going after him.

579
00:50:27,618 --> 00:50:29,970
Bullshit.
Someone asked you to kill him.

580
00:50:30,618 --> 00:50:32,525
I did it alone, for the world.

581
00:50:33,783 --> 00:50:35,431
Because you guys don't work.

582
00:50:35,790 --> 00:50:36,673
Don't say bullshit.

583
00:50:37,189 --> 00:50:39,642
Don't make excuses like that.

584
00:50:41,353 --> 00:50:43,744
Can I have a cigarette?

585
00:50:51,952 --> 00:50:53,952
Damn it.

586
00:50:54,710 --> 00:50:56,281
I wanted to kill UBE.

587
00:50:57,171 --> 00:50:58,351
My feelings were half-hearted.

588
00:50:59,991 --> 00:51:01,999
Leave it to OSAKI from now on.

589
00:51:03,343 --> 00:51:09,015
If you're happy with the UBE being killed, then you can leave now.

590
00:51:13,272 --> 00:51:16,889
Before I decide that, why do you hate FUKAZAWA so much?

591
00:51:18,233 --> 00:51:19,124
Tell me.

592
00:51:20,210 --> 00:51:22,944
Yeah,It's time you had a talk.

593
00:51:31,539 --> 00:51:36,563
It was shortly after the war ended.

594
00:51:38,414 --> 00:51:42,617
My father took care of Fukazawa, who called himself a Manchurian Ronin

595
00:51:44,637 --> 00:51:50,036
I used my father in Fukasawa to do all kinds of business.

596
00:51:50,840 --> 00:51:53,770
Smugglers, black market finance...

597
00:51:55,239 --> 00:51:57,801
He learned to make money by breaking the law.

598
00:51:58,809 --> 00:52:03,270
It may have been his inborn talent.

599
00:52:06,409 --> 00:52:11,519
And he seduced my mother.

600
00:52:15,042 --> 00:52:18,480
My foolish mother..
She left me and went into Fukazawa.

601
00:52:20,097 --> 00:52:21,730
My father never complained.

602
00:52:22,800 --> 00:52:26,847
My father had borrowed a lot of money from Fukazawa.

603
00:52:29,933 --> 00:52:33,066
Then Fukazawa abandoned my mother.

604
00:52:37,757 --> 00:52:38,811
My mom killed herself.

605
00:52:43,554 --> 00:52:44,405
I'm sorry.

606
00:52:45,225 --> 00:52:46,147
Moreover.

607
00:52:48,022 --> 00:52:52,616
After my mother and I died, he used my house as collateral for a loan.

608
00:52:54,527 --> 00:52:55,831
I was a junior in college.

609
00:52:57,550 --> 00:53:00,831
I was studying law, and I hated him.

610
00:53:03,206 --> 00:53:08,816
But people who violate the law have many lawyers.

611
00:53:11,138 --> 00:53:16,466
Court notices, foreclosures, and forced evictions before I know anything about it.

612
00:53:18,303 --> 00:53:21,959
The law that was supposed to protect us persecuted us.

613
00:53:24,256 --> 00:53:28,678
I was disappointed in the law and quit university.

614
00:53:32,490 --> 00:53:33,443
6 years later.

615
00:53:35,279 --> 00:53:40,521
Fukasawa became the back world and boss of the economic world.

616
00:53:41,324 --> 00:53:42,511
He did it in violation of the law.

617
00:53:44,831 --> 00:53:50,222
When I decided to take my revenge on him personally.
Your father killed himself.

618
00:53:51,300 --> 00:53:52,683
Your master was murdered.

619
00:53:55,770 --> 00:53:56,520
How's your father?

620
00:54:02,075 --> 00:54:03,020
Is he dead?

621
00:54:10,522 --> 00:54:11,491
He killed himself.

622
00:54:15,209 --> 00:54:16,748
If so, I've already given up.

623
00:54:19,845 --> 00:54:22,478
Don't ask me.

624
00:54:34,039 --> 00:54:35,195
What can I do for you?

625
00:54:38,749 --> 00:54:43,546
We're brothers.
I follow you.

626
00:54:44,114 --> 00:54:45,372
What can I do for you?

627
00:54:49,185 --> 00:54:50,474
Thank you.

628
00:55:22,278 --> 00:55:24,020
Here we go.

629
00:55:26,849 --> 00:55:27,544
Here it is.

630
00:55:29,317 --> 00:55:30,856
I can't accept this.

631
00:55:31,270 --> 00:55:34,638
You don't have to hesitate.

632
00:55:35,208 --> 00:55:40,927
But for future reference, please accept this in cash.

633
00:55:42,325 --> 00:55:42,849
But...

634
00:55:44,239 --> 00:55:45,692
Please.

635
00:55:46,469 --> 00:55:47,274
Hurry up.

636
00:55:53,853 --> 00:55:54,892
Thank you.

637
00:55:57,119 --> 00:55:57,908
Excuse me.

638
00:55:58,900 --> 00:56:00,407
Why don't you take a bath?

639
00:56:00,587 --> 00:56:02,134
Please take him.

640
00:56:02,525 --> 00:56:04,244
Enjoy your bath.

641
00:56:13,349 --> 00:56:13,919
Minmin.

642
00:56:14,629 --> 00:56:18,293
Don't rush.
Go to bath first.

643
00:56:18,851 --> 00:56:20,280
My important things are in this jacket.

644
00:56:20,484 --> 00:56:22,929
I'll take care of it.

645
00:56:27,709 --> 00:56:29,342
Go to bath.

646
00:56:38,374 --> 00:56:40,483
Why don't we take a bath together again?

647
00:56:40,811 --> 00:56:45,553
I'll be there soon.
You go first.

648
00:57:04,648 --> 00:57:05,960
Why do you want to know Negoro's address?

649
00:57:07,327 --> 00:57:08,195
Wanna see him?

650
00:57:11,734 --> 00:57:15,663
I haven't been able to sleep since you told me about his misfortune.

651
00:57:17,031 --> 00:57:20,945
I don't know what to say. I want to comfort you.

652
00:57:23,202 --> 00:57:24,648
Because you still love him.

653
00:57:25,585 --> 00:57:28,632
But I can't stop my feeling.

654
00:57:31,085 --> 00:57:33,913
He left me without telling me why.

655
00:57:36,843 --> 00:57:38,811
I hated him with every fiber of my being.

656
00:57:43,179 --> 00:57:44,499
I made big mistake too.

657
00:57:47,093 --> 00:57:50,624
I want to meet him, but I think he'll give me a challenge.

658
00:57:56,862 --> 00:58:01,104
Here..
If you see him, I'd like you to tell him like this.

659
00:58:02,471 --> 00:58:04,588
I'm working hard to make up for my mistakes.

660
00:58:07,416 --> 00:58:09,268
So please be patient a little longer

661
00:58:10,315 --> 00:58:11,252
Are you going yet?

662
00:58:12,362 --> 00:58:17,987
This year, in order to get engaged to you, I have to solve this problem.

663
00:58:22,713 --> 00:58:25,463
Tenkaidai National Land...

664
00:58:28,134 --> 00:58:29,704
Hello,it's me.

665
00:58:30,743 --> 00:58:34,681
Is this Mr. Ishii from an industry magazine?

666
00:58:38,812 --> 00:58:40,734
I'm not good enough for it.

667
00:58:41,031 --> 00:58:46,140
We definitely need you for this roundtable discussion.

668
00:58:48,318 --> 00:58:51,568
A young reporter will pick you up at 5:30.

669
00:58:58,353 --> 00:58:59,127
Please.

670
00:59:19,542 --> 00:59:20,316
Get up.

671
00:59:24,128 --> 00:59:26,636
Koyama-san.
I'm glad you finally woke up.

672
00:59:28,711 --> 00:59:33,385
I'll get right to it.
You got the money from New Asia Development.

673
00:59:35,077 --> 00:59:36,977
Say the truth.

674
00:59:37,793 --> 00:59:43,633
During the day today, you cashed a check for 3 million yen at Sanba Bank

675
00:59:44,239 --> 00:59:45,173
This is the photo.

676
00:59:46,946 --> 00:59:54,124
Then you put 1 million yen of it in a fixed term deposit at Sanba Bank
and another 100 to the Dairokujuroku Bank.

677
00:59:55,172 --> 00:59:59,306
And you put the remaining 100 into a loan trust at a large investment trust bank.

678
01:00:00,700 --> 01:00:01,920
This is the photo.

679
01:00:08,994 --> 01:00:11,361
You admit the fact of corruption?

680
01:00:13,931 --> 01:00:15,825
Say Yes or no.

681
01:00:18,033 --> 01:00:19,013
Say.

682
01:00:22,976 --> 01:00:25,409
We want you to talk everything what you've done.

683
01:00:34,803 --> 01:00:35,530
Please.

684
01:00:44,209 --> 01:00:45,869
Don't you know where that is?

685
01:00:47,923 --> 01:00:56,387
That's what they did to me on the way there and on the way back. They put me under anesthesia.

686
01:00:58,747 --> 01:01:00,201
Were they 3 people?

687
01:01:00,534 --> 01:01:00,854
Yes.

688
01:01:01,707 --> 01:01:02,801
What kind of men?

689
01:01:04,544 --> 01:01:10,038
There was a guy who looked like YAKUZA, and another guy who looked like a businessman, And one other guy.

690
01:01:10,750 --> 01:01:13,537
That other guy is suspicious.

691
01:01:14,851 --> 01:01:16,258
He wore dark glasses.

692
01:01:17,130 --> 01:01:21,810
You at least remember what he's like...
His moles, his hair.

693
01:01:22,722 --> 01:01:24,888
I remember nothing.

694
01:01:27,535 --> 01:01:28,995
What did you tell them?

695
01:01:32,645 --> 01:01:33,392
Everything.

696
01:01:35,218 --> 01:01:36,518
Everything?

697
01:01:50,665 --> 01:01:58,508
Mr. Fukazawa of New Asia Development
You're calling from Tokyo.

698
01:01:59,082 --> 01:01:59,722
Who?

699
01:02:04,550 --> 01:02:06,544
Hello, Fukazawa-san, is it?

700
01:02:07,964 --> 01:02:10,603
I have something I'd like you to listen to instead of music today

701
01:02:15,057 --> 01:02:20,090
I just did what NANBADA told me to do.

702
01:02:21,111 --> 01:02:26,219
Of course, they knew if they accepted the money, they would have to obey him.

703
01:02:27,194 --> 01:02:28,220
I was wrong.

704
01:02:29,882 --> 01:02:31,215
I was something wrong.

705
01:02:35,185 --> 01:02:36,438
What do you think?

706
01:02:37,691 --> 01:02:39,531
Who are you?
Why are you doing this?

707
01:02:41,130 --> 01:02:42,777
My dad is calling me from the hell.

708
01:02:43,134 --> 01:02:43,674
Your dad?

709
01:02:44,298 --> 01:02:45,998
My ex family.

710
01:02:46,191 --> 01:02:48,691
You forget?

711
01:02:49,641 --> 01:02:54,388
A mother who cared for you died,
A family was taken from you.

712
01:02:57,105 --> 01:02:58,012
So you are...

713
01:03:00,927 --> 01:03:06,560
Some of the gems you're collecting for your antennae. There must be some diamonds that hold a grudge.

714
01:03:08,250 --> 01:03:09,550
I'll pay you back.

715
01:03:10,361 --> 01:03:11,181
See you then.

716
01:03:17,269 --> 01:03:20,889
Oh the person was he...

717
01:03:22,486 --> 01:03:25,066
Now he knows about me.

718
01:03:26,492 --> 01:03:28,132
We don't have time.

719
01:03:29,436 --> 01:03:30,829
Let's get started now.

720
01:03:32,839 --> 01:03:33,806
I'm looking forward to it.

721
01:03:36,487 --> 01:03:38,573
Hey,Koyama was dead.

722
01:03:39,513 --> 01:03:43,213
I just heard it on the radio in the car.
He was found dead in a ditch in the river.

723
01:03:45,027 --> 01:03:45,920
They killed him.

724
01:03:46,220 --> 01:03:49,602
I didn't think they would kill him in a small mountain.

725
01:03:50,670 --> 01:03:53,377
I'll use my last trump card.

726
01:03:56,641 --> 01:03:57,654
See them in person.

727
01:04:02,593 --> 01:04:03,806
He wasn't in the car.

728
01:04:04,354 --> 01:04:04,780
No?

729
01:04:12,066 --> 01:04:13,699
Hello?
Oh you.

730
01:04:15,378 --> 01:04:21,311
I came in on the early shift and the boss rushed out with Sasaki and Yoshino.

731
01:04:21,970 --> 01:04:22,904
They'll go far.

732
01:04:23,157 --> 01:04:23,624
Far?

733
01:04:25,423 --> 01:04:26,023
Where'd he go?

734
01:04:26,223 --> 01:04:28,930
He had them carry pistols.

735
01:04:29,859 --> 01:04:33,485
Besides, yesterday he was showing off this amazing diamond to the manager.

736
01:04:33,991 --> 01:04:35,944
He said it used to belong to his ex family.

737
01:04:36,418 --> 01:04:36,891
What?

738
01:04:40,363 --> 01:04:43,476
I see.
Thanks for telling me.

739
01:04:44,076 --> 01:04:46,936
Do you come tonight?

740
01:04:48,345 --> 01:04:51,372
You don't know?

741
01:04:52,771 --> 01:04:56,944
Don't do anything dangerous.
I'm worried about you.

742
01:04:58,717 --> 01:05:05,410
Say something.
Hello? Hello? Hello?

743
01:05:13,641 --> 01:05:15,688
Oh ken. what?

744
01:05:16,849 --> 01:05:18,096
He doesn't get off?

745
01:05:18,729 --> 01:05:21,776
I've been looking for you a long time, I'm sure of it.
He's got to be a stopover.

746
01:05:23,412 --> 01:05:25,238
Go to Mt.Hakuun.

747
01:05:25,578 --> 01:05:26,392
Mt.Hakuun?

748
01:05:27,489 --> 01:05:30,315
There's his Villa at the peak of there.

749
01:05:31,081 --> 01:05:33,634
I'm sure he goes there and he called Nanbada.

750
01:05:34,405 --> 01:05:35,165
Nanbada too?

751
01:05:36,555 --> 01:05:39,322
I'm sure he's got everyone there working on a plan to deal with me.

752
01:05:40,774 --> 01:05:43,988
We'll break into there.
Come back now.

753
01:05:50,225 --> 01:05:50,691
Who?

754
01:06:07,387 --> 01:06:08,240
What can I do for you?

755
01:06:09,402 --> 01:06:13,842
I was confused but I wanted to see you.

756
01:06:15,728 --> 01:06:16,428
May I?

757
01:06:19,108 --> 01:06:19,581
Come in.

758
01:06:29,283 --> 01:06:34,143
I am a man who has no use for your old sweet memories.

759
01:06:35,286 --> 01:06:37,673
I heard from Osaki about you.

760
01:06:41,437 --> 01:06:44,410
That was a dramatic story worthy of the collapse of a former family, wasn't it?

761
01:06:45,523 --> 01:06:47,850
Don't say that.

762
01:06:49,745 --> 01:06:53,832
I don't know what you're talking about.
But I want to comfort you.

763
01:06:54,022 --> 01:06:55,935
It's too late.

764
01:06:57,816 --> 01:07:01,569
The one who stole my youth, stole you, stole my future.

765
01:07:02,943 --> 01:07:06,496
I can't stop about my frustration.

766
01:07:09,743 --> 01:07:14,803
Please leave.
We live in a different world now.

767
01:07:15,893 --> 01:07:18,100
Outside of law and inside.

768
01:07:18,796 --> 01:07:25,216
I know this much.
What you're doing is wrong.

769
01:07:28,241 --> 01:07:29,801
Please leave everything to OSAKI.

770
01:07:31,942 --> 01:07:36,169
I do things my way.

771
01:07:42,226 --> 01:07:46,019
I may look like a crazy person.

772
01:07:52,768 --> 01:07:56,162
I have something to show you.
Can you follow me?

773
01:07:58,288 --> 01:07:58,814
Here.

774
01:08:04,107 --> 01:08:05,060
Mental hospital.

775
01:08:06,102 --> 01:08:11,009
Mentally ill patients, abandoned by their families, are being admitted to the hospital in a similar fashion to incarceration.

776
01:08:17,401 --> 01:08:20,034
Hey get out!

777
01:08:31,703 --> 01:08:32,623
This way, please.

778
01:08:41,964 --> 01:08:48,524
Give me my XXXXXX!
Give me my XXXXXX!

779
01:08:56,802 --> 01:09:01,089
This is my last secret that I never told anyone.

780
01:09:05,634 --> 01:09:06,621
Money.

781
01:09:11,481 --> 01:09:15,061
You see?
He's almost crazy.

782
01:09:16,518 --> 01:09:18,518
I'm determined to get revenge in my own way.

783
01:09:23,590 --> 01:09:25,343
I'm going into the enemy's main camp.

784
01:09:26,405 --> 01:09:29,672
Lose or win, Osaki will have to handle it.

785
01:09:31,677 --> 01:09:33,717
Please give this to him.

786
01:09:35,832 --> 01:09:36,405
Nurse.

787
01:09:40,526 --> 01:09:43,312
Give that patient something good to eat with it.

788
01:09:44,032 --> 01:09:44,865
I beg you.

789
01:09:45,876 --> 01:09:47,822
I'll see you there.

790
01:10:22,991 --> 01:10:23,798
Here's here.

791
01:10:24,408 --> 01:10:25,522
Sorry I'm late.

792
01:10:26,383 --> 01:10:30,310
I finally find who he is.

